PROGRAM:

import java.util.Scanner;
public class addsub {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        System.out.println("Enter two numbers:");
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int num1=sc.nextInt();
        int num2=sc.nextInt();
        int addition= num1+num2;
        int subtraction= Math.abs (num1-num2);
        System.out.println("Addition of " +num1 +"and" +num2 +"is" +addition); 
        System.out.println("Subtraction of " +num1 +"and" +num2 +"is" +subtraction); 
        sc.close();
    }
}


OUTPUT:
Enter two numbers:
4
5
Addition of 4 and 5 is 9
Subtraction of 4 and 5 is 1

DESCRIPTION:
This is simple program to perform both addition and subtraction of two numbers which has been entered by the user.
it displays the output of the Addition and Subtraction of two if the result of the subtraction is in the negative values it displays as positive value.
